2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - Frequency hopping is a technique used in wireless communication networks. The paper may discuss the impact of frequency hopping sequences on network performance, which falls under the domain of social and information networks. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with frequency hopping in wireless communication systems, which is a key aspect of networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents new combinatorial constructions for frequency hopping sequence sets, which involves the use of mathematical structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper may discuss the computational complexity of the proposed constructions for frequency hopping sequence sets.
